    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin discs</p><p>Add the<strong> sliced potatoes</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 6-8 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hearty-sausage-and-baked-bean-hotpot-with-minty-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, use scissors to chop your <strong>sausages</strong> into thirds into the dish and cook for 5-6 min or until beginning to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hearty-sausage-and-baked-bean-hotpot-with-minty-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Strip your<strong> mint</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Tip: Hold the top of the herb sprigs firmly and slide your fingers down their lengths to easily remove the leaves</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>cannellini</strong> <strong>beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hearty-sausage-and-baked-bean-hotpot-with-minty-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly browned, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>drained cannellini beans</strong> with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hearty-sausage-and-baked-bean-hotpot-with-minty-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[400ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>to the dish with your <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong>,<strong> soy sauce </strong>and<strong> chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>salt </strong>and mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>sausage and bean filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hearty-sausage-and-baked-bean-hotpot-with-minty-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the sausage and bean filling with the <strong>sliced potatoes</strong> and sprinkle over your <strong>dried thyme</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven, lid off, for 20-25 min or until the potatoes and sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>hearty sausage & baked bean hotpot</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the dried thyme or only use a little!</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hearty-sausage-and-baked-bean-hotpot-with-minty-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>When the hotpot is almost ready, reboil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a pot, cover them with boiling water (just enough to cover them), bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 1 min or until they're warmed through</p><p>Once ready, drain and return to the pot, then stir through a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> with the <strong>chopped mint</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the fresh mint!</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hearty-sausage-and-baked-bean-hotpot-with-minty-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>hearty sausage & baked bean hotpot </strong>with the<strong> minty peas</strong> to the side</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Go easy on the pepper!</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
